The paper deals with the state complexity of regular operations, which is a topic in formal language theory (cs.FL). It also involves the use of finite automata, which is a common tool in data structures (cs.DS). The paper discusses the complexity of operations such as concatenation, union, and complement, which are fundamental concepts in computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of witnesses and the analysis of worst-case complexity are topics in logic and set theory (cs.LO). Finally, the paper also involves information theory, as it discusses the number of distinct transformations induced by letters in the input languages (cs.IT).
